**Abstract:**
Personal statement of goals for the next two years dated January 1997. Articulates commitment to teaching Introduction to Philosophy rather than 400-level courses to help students lead "examined lives." Discusses book project on philosophy of religion critiquing how God is typically presented as matter of intellectual assent rather than as the God believers actually pray to. Acknowledges difficulty of project and dissatisfaction with current progress.

**AI Recommendation:** Important autobiographical statement; documents book manuscript project.

